INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (857,1,'2017-06-28 19:16:51','2017-06-28 19:16:51','We respect the privacy of all who choose to visit our web site. Listed below is our company policy for everyone who chooses to access the services we offer on our Web site.\n<h3>Visitor Tracking</h3>\nWe place great importance on visitor privacy and security. We do not require site registration by visitors and we do not pass personal information about individual users to any third party. We reserve the right to perform statistical analysis of user behavior in order to measure consumer interest in the various areas of our site, and to inform advertisers as to how many consumers have seen or clicked on their advertising banners and/or rate-quoting forms. In performance of this analysis, we will disclose information to third parties only in aggregate form; no individual information will be given. Visitors IP addresses are only used to gather broad demographic user information.\n<h3>Ads &amp; Cookie Technology</h3>\nCookies, which are very small files sent to your Web browser by a site\'s server, enable more efficient ad processing, letting us streamline many of our ad presentations so you won\'t have to see the same ads over and over again. Cookies cannot get information from your hard drive without your permission, destroy files, or send you viruses. Some of our advertising is delivered using cookies. We count the number of its readers who view and click on ads, use cookies to deliver content specific to your interests, and to save your password so you don\'t have to reenter it each time you visit our site.\n<h3>Contact Information</h3>\nOur site\'s Contact form requires users to give us contact information such as name, address, phone number and e-mail address. The customer\'s contact information is used to contact the visitor for informational purposes only. Users may choose not to provide this information if they wish not to. Unique identifiers (such as social security numbers) are collected to verify the user\'s identity only and are not used for any other purpose. Demographic and profile data are also collected at our site. We use this data to tailor the visitor\'s experience at our site, showing them content that we think they might be interested in, and displaying the content according to their preferences. Personally identifiable information collected by cookies and site-analysis tools are stored in electronic logs behind our firewall, but are not sold and can be accessed by our staff only.\n<h3>E-mail Address Privacy</h3>\nWe receives many e-mail messages from our readers. We do not sell or otherwise release the names or e-mail addresses of users who write to the site. Your correspondence with us remains private.\n<h3>Surveys</h3>\nWe periodically conduct user surveys on our site, and ask visitors for contact information (like their e-mail address). The customer\'s contact information is used to contact the visitor when necessary. Users may opt-out of receiving future communications. Our online surveys ask visitors for contact information (like their e-mail address). The customer\'s contact information is used to contact the visitor only when necessary. Users may opt-out of receiving future communications. We use the information gathered surveys to help us create a better environment for our users.\n<h3>Links to Other Sites</h3>\nThis site contains links to other sites whose privacy policies may differ from ours. We encourage our readers to check the privacy policies of these sites before disclosing any personal information.\n<h3>Company Information</h3>\nWhen a company requests information about advertising on our site, we ask that you give us your company name, address, and phone number. We use this information only to contact you with information you have requested; we do not release anyone\'s name or address if they request advertising information.\n<h3>Opt-Out Procedures</h3>\nWe provides users the opportunity to opt-out of receiving communications from us. This site gives users the following options for removing their information from our database: to not receive future communications, or to no longer receive our service. You can send e-mail to: info@bizbudding.com. This site gives users the option to change and modify information previously provided.\n<h3>Corrections/Contacting the Site Administrator</h3>\nIf you have any questions about this Privacy Policy statement or the practices of this site, or if you have corrections to any of the information that you have provided us, you can contact us at info@bizbudding.com.\n\nMaiPro.io is a division of BizBudding Inc.','Privacy Policy','','trash','closed','closed','','privacy-policy__trashed','','','2018-04-17 14:50:16','2018-04-17 14:50:16','',0,'https://demo.maipro.io/lifestyle/?page_id=857',0,'page','',0);
